			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Shloyme Perkal, recorded on 12 November 1939 and describing his experiences in Międzyrzec Podlaski at the time of the
					German invasion of Poland, including bombardments and mass casualties as well as the arrival of refugees who fled other bombed out
					areas. He and several comrades attempted to go to Warsaw, but when their route was blocked, they made their way to Lublin and then
					to Chełm. He attempted to join the army in Chełm, but was then redirected to Kovel.</p>
			</abstract>
